Four people have been injured in a collision involving a taxi and car, said a paramedics service.
The incident, said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring, had taken place on the M13 in Pinetown, KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday morning.
READ: Three injured in taxi accident
"Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the taxi lying on its side in the middle of the road. A light motor vehicle was found parked a short distance away."
He said that paramedics had assessed the patients and found that four people from the taxi had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate.
READ: Two men killed in taxi accident
"The two occupants from the light motor vehicle were assessed and found to have escaped injury. The patients were treated for their injuries and were thereafter transported to RK Khan Provincial Hospital for further treatment."
He said that local authorities had been on the scene for further investigations.
